CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, January 28, 1961, pg. 12 reads: "On Top Again - Fresh from their seventh consecutive triumph, the front-running South Hills High School basketball entry of Coach Bruce Weston knocked off Allegheny High on Tuesday of this week, 74:52. Starter are, from left: Paul Rue, Ray Sineway, John Carr, Ulna Calloway and Carl Wade.  Calloway and Wade contributed 20 points each, to pace the Ruth St. entry to its 7-won-none-lost mark at the season's half-way point.  The 1961 record is a continuation of a team-winning record that has become traditional. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of five South Hills basketball players;  Paul Rue, Ray Sineway, John Carr, Ulna Calloway, and Carl Wade
